  "impact_on_program": {
    "Mpad": "t=1 \u21d2 M_pad\u22642 deployed; multipads only on CS/A_SP fibers; residual t=1 OPEN at free_core\u226b1",
    "kappa": "Ledger-native \u03ba_raw = high[0] = \u2212p_1 (Newton); need compression to [2176] or \u22642176 residual highs",
    "next": "Prove residual A_SP multipad cores are pairwise disjoint (t=1), or bound # residual highs by K_max via ledger first-match"
  },
  "lemmas": {
    "OPEN": {
      "name": "OPEN_kappa_Kmax_and_residual_t1",
      "statement": "(1) Compress ledger-native high[0]=\u2212p_1 (or exclusive first-match witness) into [2176] without collisions on residual highs, or prove \u2264K_max residual highs.\n(2) Residual multipad point-multiplicity t=1 at free_core=846161 (\u21d2 M_pad\u22642), or other residual constraint forcing near-disjoint multipad cores on A_SP.",
      "status": "OPEN"
    },
    "e2": {
      "name": "e2_high_equals_p1",
      "proof": [
        "e\u22121=1: high=(a1,) with a1=\u2212(r+s) for the free-1 pair family.",
        "Distinct highs \u21d4 distinct a1 \u21d4 distinct p_1."
      ],
      "statement": "When e=2, free-1 high is a single coefficient a1=\u2212p_1, so highs are bijective with their p_1 values. \u03ba=high[0] completely separates free-1 highs (still in F_p, not [e]).",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "exclusive": {
      "name": "fiber_exclusive_cover_witness_definition",
      "proof": [
        "By definition exclusive r lies in only one active high's cover in z.",
        "Toys: exclusive often missing or colliding across fibers when used as \u03ba."
      ],
      "statement": "In a fiber z, let Cover(H) be the union of free-1 sides of high H that appear in z. An index r \u2208 Cover(H) is exclusive if r \u2209 Cover(H') for all other highs H' active in z. Any exclusive r is a fiber-native witness for H. Existence is not guaranteed; global uniqueness of min exclusive across fibers is not guaranteed.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "locus": {
      "name": "multipads_only_on_CS_pair_fibers",
      "proof": [
        "Definition of multipad: \u22652 cores for one side key (high,c0U,c0V).",
        "Side key exists only when a free-1 CS ordered pair is present.",
        "No CS pair \u21d2 no side key \u21d2 M_pad:=1 by convention, N_ord=0.",
        "v17: Fib = A_SP \u2294 R_sing; R_sing is matching-free."
      ],
      "statement": "A multipad event requires a free-1 CS ordered pair (U,V), hence a fiber whose free-1 pencil has \u22652 members. Fibers with no top-seam CS pair (matching-free / R_sing style) have N_ord=0 and M_pad=1 vacuously. Multipad control is only needed on A_SP / top-seam fibers.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "newton": {
      "kappa_note": "So \u03ba_raw = high[0] is the ledger-native first Newton coordinate of the free-1 family \u2014 not an arbitrary hash. Still F_p-valued; reducing mod K loses injectivity (v27 bank).",
      "name": "free1_high_newton_invariants",
      "proof": [
        "Free-1 high fixes monic coeffs of X^{e\u22121},...,X^1; only c0 varies.",
        "Newton\u2013Girard: p_1,...,p_{e\u22121} are triangular functions of e_1,...,e_{e\u22121} hence of the free-1 high (p > e deployed).",
        "Explicitly p_1 = sum roots and monic coeff of X^{e\u22121} is \u2212p_1."
      ],
      "statement": "For a free-1 high H and any U \u2208 F_H, the monic free-1 coefficients of \u039b_U are (H, c0(U)), and the power sums p_k(U) for k=1,...,e\u22121 depend only on H. In particular high[0] = \u2212p_1(U) for every U \u2208 F_H (with monic product convention \u039b = \u220f(X\u2212r)).",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "t_packing": {
      "deployed": {
        "floor_n_minus_2e_over_mc": 2,
        "open": "t=1 at free_core\u226b1 on residual A_SP multipads",
        "t1_gives_Mpad_le": 2
      },
      "name": "M_pad_point_multiplicity_packing",
      "proof": [
        "Double count pairs (core, root\u2208core): left M_pad\u00b7m_c; right \u2264 t\u00b7|D\\(U\u222aV)| = t(n\u22122e).",
        "t=1 \u21d4 cores pairwise disjoint (each root in \u22641 core).",
        "free_core=1 \u21d2 |C\u2229C'|=0 (v27) \u21d2 t=1 \u21d2 packing bound (v26)."
      ],
      "statement": "Fix multipad sides (U,V). Let t = max_r |{multipad cores C \u220b r}| over r \u2208 D\\(U\u222aV). Then M_pad \u2264 \u230at(n\u22122e)/m_c\u230b. In particular t=1 \u21d2 M_pad \u2264 \u230a(n\u22122e)/m_c\u230b (= 2 deployed).",
      "status": "PROVED"
    }
  },
